msgctxt "781	TEXT"
msgid "Sometimes while driving a passenger, they may strike up a conversation with you. Press <Action:Button_Circle@Drive_Taxi>, <Action:Button_Triangle@Drive_Taxi>, or <Action:Button_Square@Drive_Taxi> to answer them. If you select the answer that best fits the situation, the passenger will have a better impression of you. The icon at the top right of the screen indicates how the passenger feels about you at the current moment."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1208	TEXT"
msgid "Sometimes while driving, you will see penalties appear on the right side of the screen. The following are subject to penalties and affect the passenger's impression of you, so drive carefully:\n"
"-Sudden acceleration　　　-Rule violations (stop signs) \n"
"-Sudden hazards　　　　　　-Leaving the road\n"
"-Sudden braking　　　　　　-Ignoring red lights\n"
"-Driving the wrong way　　　-Striking an object\n"
"-Sudden swerving　　　　　-Turning without signaling"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1676	TEXT"
msgid "When the blue gauge to the left of the speedometer fills up, you can press <Action:Button_Cross@Drive_Race> to use your turbo boost. Turbo power builds up gradually over time. While using turbo boosts, you can accelerate beyond the usual limit, so time your boosts appropriately."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1956	TEXT"
msgid "Sometimes an icon like the one above will appear on the screen. This means you have a chance to trigger a Racing Heat Action. These can be triggered on blue sections in the map on the lower left. There are a variety of Racing Heat Actions that are triggered in different ways. Use them well to gain the upper hand. <Action:Button_R2@Drive_Race> appears when a Racing Heat Action is about to end. Your speed will drop unless you keep holding down the button, so take care."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2428	TEXT"
msgid "You can drive forward using <Action:Button_R2@Drive_Taxi>. If you press it too quickly you will accelerate suddenly, upsetting your passengers, so take it easy when accelerating."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2607	TEXT"
msgid "You must stop at red lights. If you drive through one, you will suffer a heavy penalty. Use <Action:Button_L2@Drive_Taxi> to brake. Just like with the accelerator, if you press it too quickly, you will brake suddenly and upset your passengers. It is best to slow down as gradually as you can before stopping."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2916	TEXT"
msgid "You must stop at red lights. If you drive through one, you will suffer a heavy penalty."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3004	TEXT"
msgid "<Sign:8> marks indicate that no entry is allowed. You cannot drive your car into these areas. If you attempt to enter them, your position will be reset, and you will suffer a heavy penalty."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3194	TEXT"
msgid "Hold <Action:Button_LS_Left@Drive_Race> or <Action:Button_LS_Right@Drive_Race> while holding down <Action:Button_Circle@Drive_Race> to drift. You will continue to drift while <Action:Button_Circle> is held down, so use this skillfully to take corners quicker. If you drift for a set amount of time, you will receive a speed boost after you finish drifting."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3551	TEXT"
msgid "When your destination appears on the screen, stop on top of it. Take care not to drive past it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3647	TEXT"
msgid "You must come to a full stop wherever there are stop markings on the road. Drive safely to improve your passenger's impression of you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3782	TEXT"
msgid "When turning left or right, you should signal first. Use <Action:Button_DPad_Left@Drive_Taxi> when turning left, and <Action:Button_DPad_Right@Drive_Taxi> when turning right. You receive points for signaling when turning, so be sure not to forget."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4030	TEXT"
msgid "You must come to a full stop wherever there are stop markings on the road. Drive safely to improve your customer's impression of you. Use <Action:Button_L2@Drive_Taxi> to brake. Just like with the accelerator, if you press it too quickly, you will brake suddenly and upset your passengers. It is best to slow down as gradually as you can before stopping."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4385	TEXT"
msgid "Victory Conditions:\n"
"Unlike regular races, you win this race by overtaking the other car within the time limit.\n"
"\n"
"Loss Conditions:\n"
"You lose if time runs out or if the other car gets too far ahead."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4580	TEXT"
msgid "Victory Conditions:\n"
"You win if you aren't overtaken within the time limit.\n"
"\n"
"Loss Conditions:\n"
"You lose if the other car overtakes you even once."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4724	TEXT"
msgid "Haul the food stall to the goal. Unlike regular taxi missions, there are no penalties for:\n"
"\n"
"-Sudden acceleration\n"
"-Sudden braking\n"
"-Sudden swerving\n"
"-Turning without signaling\n"
"\n"
"Because there is no conversation, you also won't receive bonus points for choosing answers. You will be able to focus on getting the food stall to the goal safely."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5062	TEXT"
msgid "You are free to drive where you like.\n"
"\n"
"When you want to go back, press the <Action:Button_Touchpad@Drive_Race> button followed by <Action:Button_Triangle@UI> button to return to the office."
msgstr ""

